<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_5625bb9e-e3e0-41fa-81ff-be5bd483915a" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>H2D8</sptc><title id="_75b49367-8aa6-43c1-85db-5627d8480f37">External waterproofing</title><archive-num>2019: 3.8.1.3</archive-num><subclause id="_4d2e3a90-78c8-4652-b996-882a7858735e" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b2abdf60-e5d2-4217-99e9-ca608b844c16">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1395_4.0.0.xml#_f7304862-3529-49d7-9f62-352bcbcb6294" id="_99416129-f99b-4f96-ae66-847dceb85447" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Requirement</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1829_2.4.0.xml#_c78db730-5473-4624-a33f-2237c86f4944" id="_633376ec-f190-40bf-918c-dba66f0f072c" scope="local" type="clause">H2P2</xref> is satisfied for the design and construction of external waterproofing for roofing systems on flat roofs, roof terraces, balconies and terraces and other similar horizontal surfaces located above internal spaces of a building provided—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_b57fdfa2-0d12-4fb3-9115-f1e81fafa11f"><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_021fc64d-b8f6-4411-b27e-51623d2fa584" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membranes</xref> used in the external <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4652_0.8.0.xml#_9786edfd-014d-4144-bb1c-bc7b6a43aa5a" id="_47460815-6dec-46f8-a81a-e0408396df6c" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproofing system</xref> comply with AS 4654.1; and </li><li id="_46171b2a-b759-4cb0-9579-2683ac9c6ea4">the design and installation of the external <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4652_0.8.0.xml#_9786edfd-014d-4144-bb1c-bc7b6a43aa5a" id="_526b6611-aeed-4216-886a-84d1b87666e6" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproofing system</xref> is in accordance with AS 4654.2.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_969c44f7-e8cb-4034-ba23-bb0f13a6915d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_8dae280e-f242-4388-885f-c995bea77f19">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The requirements of (1) apply to—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_e2534bab-e9e4-4fd0-a0be-53bb82fef5aa">roofing systems other than those complying with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1810_2.31.0.xml#_db0c09bf-b7ea-46b9-aae9-6d93913efaab" id="_6b9927f6-95b0-4a93-9f7b-a100cd3245e3" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">H1D7(2)</xref> and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1810_2.31.0.xml#_51ca7a80-a0a4-4bf6-8739-5c53b9741534" id="_4ffe5a33-9179-40e0-9f90-d7cf1a6bdb55" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">(3)</xref>; and</li><li id="_bf0c7261-ddeb-44f3-9b2f-a12f97d06785">terraces, balconies and the like other than—<ol><li id="_df9cffb1-b19e-4dd9-854b-3b2aaf2d8012">a concrete slab that has a minimum step-down of 50 mm below the internal floor level; or</li><li>a suspended concrete slab—<ol><li>where the subfloor space is not used for habitable or non-habitable purposes; and</li><li>that has a minimum step-down of 50 mm below the internal floor level; or</li></ol></li><li>spaced decking in conjunction with framing members that are suitable for external use.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><callout id="_e97614ec-f32b-4e95-943d-232870614cba"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>The design of occupiable roof-top spaces, decks, balconies, particularly where located over internal spaces of a building, can be susceptible to potential for water ingress into a building and causing damage. Therefore, careful consideration should be given to the design, construction and the materials used to minimise the potential for water ingress to spaces below.</p><p>H2D8 prescribes external waterproofing requirements for buildings, and references AS 4654 Parts 1 and 2 that provide solutions for liquid and/or sheet <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_b2fc4049-b1cf-4efd-8483-9667220e3640" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref> roofing systems on flat roofs, roof terraces, balconies and terraces located over <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1326_0.4.0.xml#_b8eec66f-9c05-425d-8474-e6a2dfc2c0f4" id="_d4e291b4-e745-428d-a630-1cc138092a4f" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">habitable rooms</xref>. The term flat roof is commonly used to describe a near flat roof with enough pitch to provide drainage for rainwater.</p><p>AS 4654.1 sets out the requirements for materials forming part of a <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4652_0.8.0.xml#_9786edfd-014d-4144-bb1c-bc7b6a43aa5a" id="_67eacbc1-8e1e-457a-9fd8-3ac1da393d3b" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproofing system</xref> and AS 4654.2 sets out design and construction/installation requirements.</p><p>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1396_4.0.0.xml#_e3f95f1d-e1cc-4ab3-961d-c99a213a1de3" id="_e4c5f181-8bbe-4bb1-a021-e59a44cbee69" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Solution</xref> in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1574_2.26.0.xml#_f28c27da-3fb4-480a-b186-9ca843099473" id="_c422476a-0b18-40e9-b97c-93514e116bd2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">A2G2</xref> would need to be provided for other types of external waterproofing materials and designs.</p></callout></clause>